content: Wrote a complete `pyproject.toml` defining project metadata, core scientific dependencies (numpy/scipy/sympy/networkx/matplotlib/pandas), and a runnable console entry point `qemerge` mapped to `cli:main`, using a `src/` layout compatible with both packages and a top-level `cli.py` module.

output.code:
from pathlib import Path
import json

target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('pyproject.toml')
target_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

chunks = [
"""[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=68", "wheel"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta\"""",
"""[project]
name = "generated_script_1766430415667"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "Prototype numerical/symbolic experiments: toy Ising emergence and entanglement-graph geometry diagnostics."
readme = "README.md"
requires-python = ">=3.10"
license = {text = "MIT"}
authors = [{name = "OpenAI Code Interpreter"}]
dependencies = [
  "numpy>=1.24",
  "scipy>=1.10",
  "sympy>=1.12",
  "networkx>=3.1",
  "matplotlib>=3.7",
  "pandas>=2.0",
]

[project.scripts]
qemerge = "cli:main\"""",
"""[tool.setuptools]
package-dir = {"" = "src"}
py-modules = ["cli"]

[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
where = ["src"]
exclude = ["outputs*", "tests*"]"""
]

final_text = '\n'.join(block.strip('\n') for block in chunks).strip() + '\n'
target_path.write_text(final_text, encoding='utf-8')

print('FILE_WRITTEN:pyproject.toml')
print('DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file())))
